We prove in Theorem 5 that this quantity is also an upper bound on the prefix block-
interchange distance. To that end, we use the following notation, based on the one introduced
in [2]; for any two permutations ПҖ and Пғ, define:
вҲҶc(ПҖ, Пғ) = c(G(Пғ)) вҲ’ c(G(ПҖ)),
вҲҶc1(ПҖ, Пғ) = c1(G(Пғ)) вҲ’ c1(G(ПҖ)),
вҲҶf(ПҖ, Пғ) = f(Пғ) вҲ’ f(ПҖ), where f(ПҖ) = 0 if ПҖ fixes 1 (i.e. ПҖ1 = 1) and 1 otherwise, and
вҲҶg(ПҖ, Пғ) = g(Пғ) вҲ’ g(ПҖ).
These parameters allow us to obtain the following expression, which will be useful in our
